		<section>
			<section.front>
				<doc.title toc-guid="Id7210171682311ea83aee46e6decbb85">
					<head parent="doc.title">
						<bop/>
						<bos/>
						<label.name>§ </label.name>
						<label.designator>10:9.</label.designator>
						<headtext>Public records</headtext>
						<eos/>
						<eop/>
					</head>
				</doc.title>
			</section.front>
			<section.body>
				<para>
					<bop/>
					<bos/>
					<paratext>Public records are admissible via certified copies of the records or by testimony of someone who has compared a duplicate with the original.<eos/>
					</paratext>
					<eop/>
				</para>
				<para>
					<bop/>
					<bos/>
					<paratext>
						<cite.query w-src-number="0287017207" w-seq-number="00001" w-ref-type="LQ" w-normalized-cite="GAST24-10-1005" w-pub-number="1000468" ID="I15f942c074d311eab2f0b920da2605c5">O.C.G.A. § 24-10-1005</cite.query> reads as follows:</paratext>
					<display.quote>
						<para>
							<paratext>
								<begin.quote ID="QT_0001"/>The contents of a public record, or of a document authorized to be recorded or filed and actually recorded or filed, including data compilations in any form, if otherwise admissible, may be proved by duplicate, certified as correct in accordance with <cite.query w-src-number="0287017207" w-seq-number="00002" w-ref-type="LQ" w-normalized-cite="GAST24-9-902" w-pub-number="1000468" ID="I15fa543074d311eab2f0b920da2605c5">Code Section 24-9-902</cite.query> or <cite.query w-src-number="0287017207" w-seq-number="00003" w-ref-type="LQ" w-normalized-cite="GAST24-9-920" w-pub-number="1000468" ID="I15fa543174d311eab2f0b920da2605c5">Code Section 24-9-920</cite.query> or testified to be correct by a witness who has compared it with the original. <eos/>
								<bos/>If a duplicate which complies with this Code section cannot be obtained by the exercise of reasonable diligence, then other evidence of the contents may be given.<eos/>
								<end.quote refid="QT_0001"/>
							</paratext>
						</para>
					</display.quote>
					<eop/>
				</para>
				<para>
					<bop/>
					<bos/>
					<paratext>Of course, there are still authentication concerns. <eos/>
						<bos/>Public records are those documents made by a public officer within the scope of his official duty and include legislative, judicial, and administrative documents. <eos/>
						<bos/>Public records are only such documents as are created in the course of operation of a public office.[<eos/>
						<bos/>
						<footnote.reference refid="I7ac713d074d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5">1</footnote.reference>] They may be authenticated by evidence that a document authorized by law to be recorded or filed and in fact recorded or filed in a public office or a purported public record, report, statement, or data compilation, in any form, is from the public office where items of this nature are kept.[<eos/>
						<bos/>
						<footnote.reference refid="I7ac713d174d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5">2</footnote.reference>]</paratext>
					<eos/>
					<eop/>
				</para>
				<para>
					<bop/>
					<bos/>
					<paratext>The certificate or attestation of any state or county public officer or any clerk or keeper of county, consolidated government, or municipal records in Georgia gives sufficient validity or authenticity to any copy or transcript of any record, document, paper or file, or any matter or thing in such public officer&apos;s respective office, or pertaining thereto, to admit the same in evidence.[<eos/>
						<bos/>
						<footnote.reference refid="I7ac713d274d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5">3</footnote.reference>]</paratext>
					<eos/>
					<eop/>
				</para>
				<para>
					<bop/>
					<bos/>
					<paratext>Thus, a traffic citation charging the defendant with failure to yield right of way was admissible as a public record in a civil damage suit because the citation noted the entry of a guilty plea.[<eos/>
						<bos/>
						<footnote.reference refid="I7ac713d374d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5">4</footnote.reference>]</paratext>
					<eos/>
					<eop/>
				</para>
			</section.body>
		</section>
